n \in \mathbb{N}
2n
p + q = 2n
p\cdot q
p' = p-1
q' = q+1
q
p-1
(p-1)\cdot(q+1) - p\cdot q = p-q-1
p > q+1
p > q+1 \implies |E|<|E'|
q > p+1 \implies |E|>|E'|
p+q = 2n
|E|
p = q = n
n = 4
x,y
2s
2(x+y)=2s
xy=x(s-x)=\frac{s^2}4-(x-\frac s2)^2
(x-\frac s2)^2\ge0,xy\le\frac{s^2}4
\frac{s^2}4
x-\frac s2=0\implies x=\frac s2\implies y=s-x=\frac s2=x
A=xy=x(s-x)=sx-x^2
\frac{dA}{dx}=s-2x
A,\frac{dA}{dx}=0\implies x=\frac s2
\frac{d^2A}{dx^2}=-2<0
x=\frac s2
A
xy = \frac{1}{4}((x+y)^2-(x-y)^2)
x+y=2
xy = 1-\frac{1}{4}(x-y)^2
xy \leq 1
x=1, y=1
xy = 1
xy < 1
